{"questionId":"17523","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {x^4} - 54{x^2} + 60x\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>54</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>60</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>, for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 1 \\leqslant x \\leqslant 6\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;The following diagram shows the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e2818b3d7e5319794cf66f907e9004290f1e196a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">There are <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-intercepts at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> and at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = p\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>. There is a maximum at point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = a\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>, and a point of inflexion at point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = b\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the coordinates of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>A</mtext> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.562134\"> <mn>0.562134</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16.7641\"> <mn>16.7641</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {0.562{\\text{, }}16.8} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>0.562</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mn>16.8</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp; N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17523","referenceCode":"19N.2.SL.TZ0.S_8b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the coordinates of A .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.17—Areas under curve onto y-axis, volume of revolution (about x and y axes)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}